history.content: Hi there, hoping your classmates respond as well, but EE 130 is considered to have a reasonable workload. Historically there have been 5 problem sets and a final project w/ a significant time commitment.

It is "design" course in a sense that there is a final project, which is simulating your device performance and explaining what goes on in it. 
The workload itself varies depending on how quick you are in understanding. The p-set and design course does not take too much time. However, if you are not familiar with device, it might be difficult in terms of content. (Final project only took me ~2days only). 

But Prof.Javey is amazing! Actually the best professor as a lecturer I've had at Berkeley.
How is the workload of EE130? It is listed as a design course, so is there a final project? I've heard that it is relatively low workload, which seems to contradict the fact it is a design course.
